race.comment: BOLTED IN (5) doesn't win very often but did get home strongly last time out over this trip at Strathalbyn. Strips rock-hard fit and doesn't need to find much more to get the verdict. KISS AND KABOOM (7) proved too strong two runs ago at Gawler but was safely held last time at Bordertown. This looks a sterner test than last time but on her best form she is one of the chief contenders. ALL SHOT (2) is a lightly raced gelding resuming for the O'Connor camp. Has been readied with a nice trial effort and gets in well with the 3kg claimer engaged. Just needs some luck from the draw. LADY OF SAVOY (11) is ticking along nicely without winning and is worth following up with Holder booked. ROCKTAGON (1) was too bad to be true last start and should be kept safe on best figures.
